<section xml:id="section-special-forms-terminology">

<title>Terminology and notation</title>

<p><dl width="narrow">

	<li xml:id="definition-special-forms-scalar-matrix">
	<title>scalar matrix</title>
	<idx><h>scalar</h><h>matrix</h></idx>
	<idx><h>matrix</h><h>scalar</h></idx>
	<p> a square matrix that is equal to a scalar multiple of the identity matrix </p>
	</li>

	<li>
	<title>diagonal matrix</title>
	<idx><h>diagonal matrix</h></idx>
	<idx><h>matix</h><h>diagonal</h></idx>
	<p> a square matrix where all entries that are not on the main diagonal are equal to zero </p>
	</li>

	<li xml:id="definition-special-forms-upper-tri">
	<title>upper triangular matrix</title>
	<idx><h>upper triangular matrix</h></idx>
	<idx><h>matix</h><h>upper triangular</h></idx>
	<p> a square matrix where all entries that are below the main diagonal are equal to zero </p>
	</li>

	<li>
	<title>lower triangular matrix</title>
	<idx><h>lower triangular matrix</h></idx>
	<idx><h>matix</h><h>lower triangular</h></idx>
	<p> a square matrix where all entries that are above the main diagonal are equal to zero </p>
	</li>

	<li>
	<title>symmetric matrix</title>
	<idx><h>symmetric matrix</h></idx>
	<idx><h>matix</h><h>symmetric</h></idx>
	<p> a square matrix that is equal to its own transpose </p>
	</li>

</dl></p>

</section>
